```suggestion
@[simp]
theorem arctan_eq_zero_iff {x : ℝ} : arctan x = 0 ↔ x = 0 :=
  .trans (by rw [arctan_zero]) arctan_injective.eq_iff

theorem arctan_ne_zero {x : ℝ} (hx : x ≠ 0) : arctan x ≠ 0 :=
  arctan_eq_zero_iff.not.mpr hx
```

I wonder if we have a stated preference for closed or open intervals in integrals; if we do, we should follow it.
I extrapolated from the very small sample size of this file. Maybe we have yet to establish a convention.

I would suggest closed on the right and open on the left (as already implemented here) since [intervalIntegral](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/IntervalIntegral.html#intervalIntegral) uses `Set.Ioc` under the hood. That way if you were to subtract two of these `Set.Iic` integrals, you would get an `intervalIntegral` more easily.

I think you should prefer `(1 + x ^ 2)⁻¹` throughout this PR since that is the simp normal form. Of course, please rename the lemmas appropriately too.

Also, it's a minor point but you can strengthen this lemma to `𝓝[<] π`.

this is a special case of [integrable_rpow_neg_one_add_norm_sq](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Analysis/SpecialFunctions/JapaneseBracket.html#integrable_rpow_neg_one_add_norm_sq)

Could you move it to another section like `univFTC`, that we will maybe extend later on? This lemma doesn't really belong to `IicFTC`.
